New Records: The Philadelphia Phillies clinched their first NL East title since 2011 with a 6-2 win over the Chicago Cubs.
Kyle Schwarber and J.T. Realmuto each hit home runs during the game.
Key Match Events: Aaron Nola pitched seven strong innings, striking out seven batters.
The Philadelphia Phillies celebrated their NL East title victory on the field.
Post-Match Reflections: The Phillies' victory marked their third consecutive postseason appearance after two years of heartbreak in the World Series and NLCS.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillie Phanatic joined the celebration on the field as fans celebrated the team's division title win.
